join Teodora right
[style name="namelabel_teodora"]
Teodora: Tonight, I will tell you a story. It is about a moth...
Teodora: The mother moth warned her child not to go near the flame. But the young moth wanted to see the light in its own way.
join Rizal left
leave Teodora
[style name="new_style"]
Rizal: What happened mother?
join Teodora right
leave Rizal
[style name="namelabel_teodora"]
Teodora: It flew closer... and closer...
leave Teodora
join Rizal left
[style name="new_style"]
Rizal: Mother... why didn't he listen?
join Teodora right
leave Rizal
[style name="namelabel_teodora"]
Teodora: Because there are those who are willing to do everything... to reach the light.
join Rizal left
leave Teodora
[style name="new_style"]
Rizal: Was the moth foolish... or brave?
leave Rizal
join Teodora right
[style name="namelabel_teodora"]
Teodora: That depends on what he is willing to offer.
